#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an8.71"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an8.71:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 8 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.71:0.2"
msgid "8. Yamakavagga "
msgstr "8. Pairs "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 71. Paṭhamasaddhāsutta → paṭhamasamantapāsādikasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an8.71:0.3"
msgid "71. Paṭhamasaddhāsutta "
msgstr "71. Inspiring All Around (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
#. VAR: Saddho ca → saddho (s1-3)
#. VAR: ca → no (s1-3)
msgctxt "an8.71:1.1"
msgid "“Saddho ca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu hoti, no ca sīlavā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, a mendicant is faithful but not ethical. "

msgctxt "an8.71:1.2"
msgid "Evaṃ so tenaṅgena aparipūro hoti. "
msgstr "So they’re incomplete in that respect, "

msgctxt "an8.71:1.3"
msgid "Tena taṃ aṅgaṃ paripūretabbaṃ: "
msgstr "and should fulfill it, thinking: "

msgctxt "an8.71:1.4"
msgid "‘kintāhaṃ saddho ca assaṃ sīlavā cā’ti. "
msgstr "‘How can I become faithful and ethical?’ "

msgctxt "an8.71:1.5"
msgid "Yato ca kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saddho ca hoti sīlavā ca, "
msgstr "When the mendicant is faithful and ethical, "

msgctxt "an8.71:1.6"
msgid "evaṃ so tenaṅgena paripūro hoti. "
msgstr "they’re complete in that respect. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an8.71:2.1"
msgid "Saddho ca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu hoti sīlavā ca, no ca bahussuto. "
msgstr "A mendicant is faithful and ethical, but not learned. "

msgctxt "an8.71:2.2"
msgid "Evaṃ so tenaṅgena aparipūro hoti. "
msgstr "So they’re incomplete in that respect, "

msgctxt "an8.71:2.3"
msgid "Tena taṃ aṅgaṃ paripūretabbaṃ: "
msgstr "and should fulfill it, thinking: "

msgctxt "an8.71:2.4"
msgid "‘kintāhaṃ saddho ca assaṃ, sīlavā ca, bahussuto cā’ti. "
msgstr "‘How can I become faithful, ethical, and learned?’ "

msgctxt "an8.71:2.5"
msgid "Yato ca kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saddho ca hoti sīlavā ca bahussuto ca, "
msgstr "When the mendicant is faithful, ethical, and learned, "

msgctxt "an8.71:2.6"
msgid "evaṃ so tenaṅgena paripūro hoti. "
msgstr "they’re complete in that respect. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.315, sc3
msgctxt "an8.71:3.1"
msgid "Saddho ca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu hoti sīlavā ca bahussuto ca, no ca dhammakathiko … pe … "
msgstr "A mendicant is faithful, ethical, and learned, but not a Dhamma speaker. … "

msgctxt "an8.71:3.2"
msgid "dhammakathiko ca, no ca parisāvacaro … pe … "
msgstr "they don’t frequent assemblies … "

msgctxt "an8.71:3.3"
msgid "parisāvacaro ca, no ca visārado parisāya dhammaṃ deseti … pe … "
msgstr "they don’t teach Dhamma to the assembly with assurance … "

msgctxt "an8.71:3.4"
msgid "visārado ca parisāya dhammaṃ deseti, no ca catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī … pe … "
msgstr "they don’t get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty … "

msgctxt "an8.71:3.5"
msgid "catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī, no ca āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati; "
msgstr "they don’t realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements. "

msgctxt "an8.71:3.6"
msgid "evaṃ so tenaṅgena aparipūro hoti. "
msgstr "So they’re incomplete in that respect, "

msgctxt "an8.71:3.7"
msgid "Tena taṃ aṅgaṃ paripūretabbaṃ: "
msgstr "and should fulfill it, thinking: "

msgctxt "an8.71:3.8"
msgid "‘kintāhaṃ saddho ca assaṃ, sīlavā ca, bahussuto ca, dhammakathiko ca, parisāvacaro ca, visārado ca parisāya dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ, catunnañca jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī assaṃ akicchalābhī akasiralābhī, āsavānañca khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘How can I become faithful, ethical, and learned, a Dhamma speaker, one who frequents assemblies, one who teaches Dhamma to the assembly with assurance, one who gets the four absorptions when they want, and one who lives having realized the ending of defilements?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an8.71:4.1"
msgid "Yato ca kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saddho ca hoti, sīlavā ca, bahussuto ca, dhammakathiko ca, parisāvacaro ca, visārado ca parisāya dhammaṃ deseti, catunnañca jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī, āsavānañca khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati; "
msgstr "When they’re faithful, ethical, and learned, a Dhamma speaker, one who frequents assemblies, one who teaches Dhamma to the assembly with assurance, one who gets the four absorptions when they want, and one who lives having realized the ending of defilements, "

msgctxt "an8.71:4.2"
msgid "evaṃ so tenaṅgena paripūro hoti. "
msgstr "they’re complete in that respect. "

# NOTE: This sutta and the next are missing the opening statements that normally mirror this close.
msgctxt "an8.71:4.3"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu samantapāsādiko ca hoti sabbākāraparipūro cā”ti. "
msgstr "A mendicant who has these eight qualities is inspiring all around, and is complete in every respect.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an8.71:4.4"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

